<dl id="n11030c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11030c">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11030c"> 30(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mon ami <font face="wake">D</font> to <font face="wake">I</font> / embrace of death / sorts thing</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mon jeune ami, les mouvements d&apos;un coeur comme le tien ne sauraient &ecirc;tre &eacute;gaux; mod&egrave;re seulement ce caract&egrave;re qui t&apos;a d&eacute;j&agrave; fait tant de mal. Si tu souffres plus qu&apos;un autre des choses de la vie, il ne faut pas t&apos;en &eacute;tonner : une grande &acirc;me doit contenir plus de douleurs qu&apos;une petite. <br><font color="green">[My young friend, the impulses of such a heart as yours cannot be even: do but temper this disposition of yours which has already done you so much harm. You should not wonder that you suffer more than anyone else from the affairs of this life: a noble soul must harbour more grief than a paltry one.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i>Ren&eacute;</i> 92</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n03144a" href="n03all.htm#n03144a">N03 (VI.B.3):144(a)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
